{
  "version": 1,
  "tasks": [
    {
      "id": "RQ-0001",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Fix Quick Capture Save so first-run loop capture succeeds or reports errors",
      "description": "Dogfood ISSUE-001: On http://127.0.0.1:8000/#capture, entering text in Quick capture and clicking the primary Save button left the text in the form, did not add a loop to the Inbox, and showed no visible loading, success, or error feedback. This blocks the core first-run capture workflow.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "bug",
        "frontend",
        "capture",
        "dogfood",
        "ux",
        "first-run"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "frontend/src/surfaces/bootstrap.ts Quick Capture submit/state/reset logic",
        "frontend/index.html Quick Capture card markup and accessible status regions",
        "frontend/src/styles/components.css and frontend/src/styles/layout.css Quick Capture card/responsive styling",
        "frontend/src/surfaces/api.ts capture transport contract if test coverage requires a small assertion",
        "frontend/src/surfaces/* tests, especially a new focused Quick Capture interaction regression test",
        "src/cloop/static/dist built frontend assets if this repo expects built assets to be refreshed after frontend changes"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Dogfood evidence: dogfood-output/videos/issue-001-repro.webm and dogfood-output/screenshots/issue-001-step-1.png through issue-001-result.png show Quick Capture Save leaving text in place, adding no visible Inbox card, and showing no loading/success/error feedback.",
        "Observed against http://127.0.0.1:8000/#capture in a fresh browser session with CLOOP_DATA_DIR=/tmp/cloop-dogfood-data; direct POST /loops/capture with raw_text, captured_at, and client_tz_offset_min succeeded, so the backend route is viable.",
        "Static recon found the frontend submit path in frontend/src/surfaces/bootstrap.ts::captureLoop(), which currently builds raw_text/captured_at/client_tz_offset_min and posts via frontend/src/surfaces/api.ts::captureLoop() to POST /loops/capture.",
        "Backend contract source of truth is src/cloop/schemas/_loops/core.py::LoopCaptureRequest and src/cloop/routes/loops/lifecycle.py::loop_capture_endpoint; raw_text, captured_at, and client_tz_offset_min are required.",
        "Quick Capture currently has no dedicated frontend interaction tests; existing frontend coverage includes surfaces/api.test.ts and surfaces/loop.test.ts but not capture-form submit/pending/error/reset behavior.",
        "The served app uses Vite-built assets from src/cloop/static/dist via src/cloop/web.py; if frontend source changes are made, Phase 2 should verify whether the static dist build must be regenerated for browser dogfood to exercise the fix.",
        "Potential additional risk: frontend/public/sw.js intercepts /loops/* requests and can return a 202 offline queued shape for POST /loops/capture, so success handling must distinguish confirmed server-created loops from queued/offline captures and never silently reset on failed/server-rejected attempts."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Reproduce or instrument the Quick Capture path first: confirm whether clicking Save invokes the form submit handler, what network request is sent, whether a service worker intercepts it, and which response branch runs.",
        "Root-cause the failure before patching: inspect captureLoop(), requestJson(), service worker fetch handling, shell surface activation, and built dist freshness; fix the actual broken path rather than only changing copy.",
        "Redesign the Quick Capture card as a normal-user product form: task text is the obvious required field, Save is the clear primary action, optional details are understandable and non-distracting, and validation/status feedback lives next to the form.",
        "Implement a robust capture submission state machine: validate locally, disable Save while submitting, expose aria-busy/pending copy, send canonical /loops/capture payload with raw_text/captured_at/client_tz_offset_min, render success only after a created loop is returned, reset only after success, and leave all input intact on failure.",
        "Ensure the new loop becomes visible immediately without manual refresh: insert/replace via the canonical loop.replaceLoop()/syncInboxLoop path when filters allow it, or show clear guidance if the active filters/query hide the newly created loop.",
        "Add inline, actionable error handling for validation, network/server failures, and malformed/offline queued responses; do not let errors disappear into the generic shared status area with ambiguous copy.",
        "Add regression coverage for successful capture payload + Inbox update, failed capture feedback with preserved form state, local validation, pending/disabled Save state, and active-filter/query behavior if the new item would otherwise be hidden.",
        "Run focused frontend verification during implementation, then perform visual verification with agent_browser against the built/served app, and finish with make ci."
      ],
      "notes": [
        "Task goal: Quick Capture Save on http://127.0.0.1:8000/#capture must create a visible loop on first run or clearly report why it did not; silent no-op behavior is unacceptable for the core capture workflow.",
        "Why: first-run capture is the primary value path. If typing a task and pressing Save appears to do nothing, users cannot trust the product even though the backend API works.",
        "Acceptance criteria: typing a task and pressing Quick Capture Save creates a visible loop without manual refresh; invalid/server-failed attempts show an actionable inline error and preserve form contents; the form resets only after confirmed successful creation; regression tests prove required payload fields are posted and Inbox updates.",
        "UX direction: redesign the entire Quick Capture card where helpful, not just the broken Save path. Optimize for a normal user: obvious task entry, clear required vs optional fields, immediate pending/success/error states, and a clear indication of where the saved item went.",
        "Product surface anchors: purpose = capture a loop/task quickly; audience = normal first-run user; primary action = Save captured task; interaction thesis = calm form with one dominant text field and one reliable primary action, plus optional details that never block or distract.",
        "Do not prioritize backwards compatibility with broken/ambiguous behavior. Replace improper UI/state handling with the canonical /loops/capture contract and accessible feedback.",
        "Implementation agent may adapt the plan if files moved or recon missed a related path, but must stay on RQ-0001 and update all directly related source, tests, styles, and built assets needed for the served browser UI.",
        "Reviewed Phase 2 Quick Capture changes and fixed a notification permission retry edge case found during review.",
        "Added regression coverage for invalid due-date feedback, invalid-state clearing after recovery, and failed notification permission attempts.",
        "Verified with targeted Vitest coverage and frontend typecheck; CI gate is disabled for this Phase 3 run."
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-04-27T16:24:39.000000000Z",
