    {
      "id": "RQ-0002",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Make enrichment failure states explainable and recoverable on loop cards",
      "description": "Dogfood ISSUE-002: Newly created loop cards displayed an Enrichment failed badge with no explanation, diagnostic details, or recovery guidance. The loop itself remained usable, but the first-run task list looked broken.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "ux",
        "frontend",
        "enrichment",
        "dogfood"
      ],
      "scope": [],
      "evidence": [
        "Evidence: dogfood-output/screenshots/issue-002-result.png plus capture-with-data/inbox-with-data screenshots.",
        "Loops seeded through POST /loops/capture rendered normally aside from the unexplained Enrichment failed badge.",
        "The UI includes an Enrich button lower on each card, but the badge does not tell users whether retrying is appropriate, what provider/config failed, or whether enrichment was optional."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Inspect the loop serialization/enrichment state fields available to the frontend.",
        "Define a user-facing enrichment status treatment for disabled/skipped/failed/pending/success states.",
        "Show concise failure reason and a clear retry action when retry is possible; avoid alarming badges for optional/config-skipped enrichment.",
        "Add tests for loop-card rendering of enrichment failure/skip states and retry affordance."
      ],
      "notes": [
        "Acceptance criteria:",
        "- Loop cards explain why enrichment failed or was skipped in plain language.",
        "- Cards make clear whether the loop is still usable and what action, if any, should be taken.",
        "- Retry/enrich affordance is connected to the visible status and reports retry outcomes.",
        "- Rendering tests cover at least failed and skipped enrichment states.",
        "Direction decision from interview 2026-04-27:",
        "- Use the recommended differentiated-state approach, but choose copy and UI treatment by what a normal user expects rather than by internal implementation details.",
        "- Long-term UX target: optional AI/enrichment should never make the task itself look broken; failures should be calm, understandable, and actionable only when the user can do something useful."
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-04-27T16:24:39.000000000Z",
